<h2 align="center" class="style13 style50">WHAT'S MOBIDIS </h2>
<p align="justify" class="style14">The MOBIDIS project has the goal of designing and developing a middleware platform able to provide a communication software level and to support the development of distributed applications for Mobile Ad hoc NETworks (MANET).&#13;In particular, a workflow management system targeted to MANET and able to adaptively coordinate tasks and activities is the ultimate goal of the project. </p>
<p align="justify" class="style43"> <span class="style14">MANET is a network of mobile devices (PDAs, smartphones, laptops), in which all mobile devices communicate each other across wireless channels (802.11x, Bluetooth), not considering a backbone wired infrastructure, in a peer- to-peer fashion. &#13;&#13;Typical application scenarios range from collaborative and distributed mobile computing to disaster recovery (fire, flood, earthquake), law enforcement (crowd control, search and rescue) and digital battlefield communications relief. In that a wired infrastructure is impossible to setup.&#13;&#13;Key characteristics of these systems are team collaboration of large number of mobile units and limited bandwidth.&#13;</span></p>
<p align="justify" class="style14">The middleware MOBIDIS provides a communication's software level to allow the development of distribute application in ad hoc network of little mobile device (PDA,smartphone, laptop). This mobile device are connect in way peer-to-peer through wireless technology, without permanent infrastructure.</p>
<p align="justify" class="style14">Some scenary of application are the emergence situation and all situation where the infrastructure is a few advantageous. </p>
